Bartholin gland cyst is characterized by pain and swelling over the vulva. Atrophic vaginitis is usually seen in postmenopausal women and can present with vaginal dryness and itching. Infectious vulvovaginitis can cause discharge, but usually includes symptoms such as itching, burning and redness.
